@@ -0,0 +1,9 @@
+# Solution
+
+Successful `get` calls returned values without moving their entries to the
+most-recently-used end of the `OrderedDict`, so subsequent inserts evicted the
+wrong key. The cache now refreshes recency after a successful, non-expired read.
+
+`put` also evicted an entry whenever the cache was full, even when the key being
+written already existed. Eviction is now performed only for new keys, allowing
+updates to replace the value and refresh its recency and timestamp in place.
